parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Timing Case Profile Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine timing case profile gasket can cause coolant to leak out, leading to engine overheating, which can result in serious damage to the engine, potentially causing a breakdown or even an accident.
symptoms: loss of coolant on the roadway

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Electronic Command Control Box
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water entering the Electronic Command Control Box can cause short circuits, leading to a complete shutdown of the vehicle's systems, which can result in loss of control, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to rapidly gain speed, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own without pressing the accelerator pedal
the RPMs surge to high levels
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the vehicle is hard to control.
